<p>&#8220;The other day we had a long discourse with [Lady Orkney] about love; and she told us a saying &#8230; which I thought excellent, that in men, desire begets love, and in women, love begets desire.&#8221; &#8212; Jonathan Swift, <a href="https://books.google.com/books?id=419dXZTMghkC&#038;pg=466"><em>A Journal to Stella</em></a>, Oct. 30, 1712</p>
